# Copy to .env.local for local `vercel dev`. NEVER commit real values.
#
# Community layer (api/community.ts) — Upstash Redis via the Vercel marketplace
# integration. DO NOT paste values by hand; after connecting the integration run:
#     npx vercel link && npx vercel env pull .env.local
#
# The handler accepts either naming convention:
KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
# ...or:
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
#
# NOTE: plain `npm run dev` (vite, :8090) does NOT serve /api — the app runs in
# national-only mode there, which is by design. Use `npx vercel dev` to exercise
# the community API locally.

# ── AI insights (api/insights.ts) — OPTIONAL, free-first provider chain ──
# Any ONE of these activates the AI coach. Free options (no credit card):
#   GEMINI_API_KEY  — aistudio.google.com/apikey  (Google AI Studio free tier)
#   GROQ_API_KEY    — console.groq.com            (Groq free tier)
# Paid fallback:
#   OPENAI_API_KEY
# With no key set, the app shows deterministic insights — nothing breaks.
GEMINI_API_KEY=
GROQ_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
